title: Dildo on pitch at Tranmere football game
text:
Awks.
news.com.au GOALKEEPER Scott Davies is used to stopping balls, but he didn’t know quite what to do when a fan hurled a dildo onto the pitch.
The sex toy was thrown from the away end by Tranmere fans at Wrexham FC’s Racecourse Ground, in Wales, during the second-half of the 2-2 draw.
It was quickly cleared from the pitch by Davies, 28, but not before it had been caught on camera by Craig Colville.
“Who throws a dildo? Honestly!” Source: Supplied
Football can be dull at times, but the fans don’t need this much stimulation. Source: Supplied
Is that a dildo in your hand or are you just happy to see us? Source: Supplied
Craig said: “I was covering the game when I heard a thud.
“I saw what I thought was a carrot and thought, ‘What sort of football fan would take a carrot to a game?’
“When I realised what it was, I thought, ‘Crikey, that could have taken someone’s eye out or chipped a tooth.’”
Following the game, Wrexham town centre inspector Paul Wycherley, of North Wales Police, took to Twitter to confirm a male had been arrested “for throwing a missile onto the playing area”.
